{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 325°F. Line two baking sheets with parchment paper and set aside.","Place butter and golden syrup into mixing bowl and heat <nobr>2 min\/140°F\/speed 2<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl and blade with spatula, and heat again <nobr>1 min\/140°F\/speed 2<\/nobr>.","Add baking soda and mix <nobr>5 sec\/speed 3<\/nobr>.","Add oats, flour, sugar and coconut and mix <nobr>10 sec\/\/speed 4<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and mix again <nobr>10 sec\/\/speed 4<\/nobr>.","Form dough with aid of a tablespoon, using a heaping tablespoon per cookie. Roll into balls (approx. 30 ) and place onto prepared baking sheets 1 in. apart and gently flatten (to approx. 2 in. diameter), allowing space for cookies to spread during baking.","Bake for 8-10 minutes (325°F) until golden brown. Allow to rest on baking sheets for 5 minutes. Transfer to a wire rack to cool completely, or serve warm."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["4 oz unsalted butter, cut into pieces","3 ½ oz golden syrup","1 tsp baking soda","3 ½ oz old fashioned rolled oats","5 ½ oz all-purpose flour","2 ½ oz light brown sugar","1 oz unsweetened, finely shredded coconut"]}],"id":"r117580","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-rrfEn7U2TsM\/XZWrDeYOPeI\/AAAAAAAAfhY\/O076ieVz--cZZL1GTj6GzgwtYq1gdt7aACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_bCAAym35BXNiO5ZA.png","title":"Anzac Cookies","publishedAt":"2017-03-17T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"1 g","fat":"4.7 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"11 g","calories":"377 kJ \/ 90 kcal"},"usefulItems":"parchment paper, wire rack, baking sheets (approx. 16 in. x 14 in.), oven","hintsAndTricks":["The Anzac biscuit is a sweet biscuit which is popular in Australia and New Zealand. The original biscuit was not sweet at all; rather it was a savory hardtack biscuit (also known as an Anzac tile or wafer) that was used in Australian and New Zealand Army Corps (ANZAC) soldiers’ rations as a substitute for bread in World War I.","Store cookies in an airtight container until ready to use.<br>- Golden syrup can be found in Cost Plus World Market and some Safeway stores."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","30m","30 pieces"]}